{
  "category": "Uncategorized",
  "description": "Fix Menu Internationalization - Ensure English Translation\n\nResolve the issue where menu items are not displaying in English, ensuring proper internationalization support is implemented.\n\nRequirements:\n- Identify which menu components are not being translated (main navigation, dropdown menus, context menus, etc.)\n- Verify English translation strings exist in the language resource files\n- Ensure the i18n/localization library is properly configured and connected to menu components\n- Check that the correct language locale is being detected or set to English\n- Verify all menu items, labels, and tooltips are using translation keys rather than hardcoded text\n- Test menu display with English locale to confirm all items appear correctly\n- Check for any fallback language issues if English translations are missing\n\nEdge Cases to Consider:\n- Dynamic menu items generated from data\n- Nested or multi-level menu structures\n- Menu items that appear conditionally based on user state\n- Keyboard shortcuts or accessibility labels associated with menus",
